	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Mon May 06, 2013 6:18 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Need help for MMC5 advanced features</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />If you want to show all tiles unique, there are two ways to do it: <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha"><li>Sprite 0 or scanline interrupts triggering a tile bank change during hblank. This has been used since MMC1 if not earlier for title screens and is seen in, for example, Smash TV's title screen. </li><li>Use the MMC5's third nametable to specify the attribute and top 6 bits of the tile number. This &quot;ExGrafix&quot; mode is exclusive to the MMC5 and is the only way to properly show a box of ideographic text without either CHR RAM, precomposing all sentences, or using huge pixels as in <a href="http://bootleggames.wikia.com/wiki/Jing_Ke_Xin_Zhuan" class="postlink">Jing Ke Xin Zhuan (荊軻新傳)</a>. </li></ol>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
