		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Need help for MMC5 advanced features</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"> Sprite 0 or scanline interrupts triggering a tile bank change during hblank. This has been used since MMC1 if not earlier for title screens and is seen in, for example, Smash TV's title screen. </div><br /><br />If you use something with smaller than 4KB CHR banks the timing doesn't need to be as precise.  With something like MMC3 and using 2KB background banks you could just swap banks one or few scanlines before the switch so long as the tiles at the seam are from different banks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
